{
  "stem": "11274.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So this is the last time, on the street, that I saw him, is Andrej.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, then I came home after this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A couple of months later, I came home because I heard rumors they're going to displace all the Jews away from Tylicz, because Tylicz and [?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Welshinka ?] are too close to the-- to the Slovakian border.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And apparently, some Jews escaped or something, and they probably noticed me, too, disappearing, there in Russia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they don't trust the Jews anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And you can go anywhere you want to-- [COUGH] Excuse me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[COUGHING] [DRINKS] 25 kilometers away from the border.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You can take with you-- we-- remember, we dug out potatoes and there was a full cellar of potatoes still in the winter.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It's in the fall the next year, but there were still some potatoes there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] And, and you can-- when I came home.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I had a guide, another guide hired, my uncle hired, and then I came home, because their parents were elderly.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I said, I can do a lot more for them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I can sew to earn some money too, for, for a living.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] And then you can take one loaf of bread and you can take one change of clothes, you can take 500 zlotys.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But the zlotys wasn't a problem because we didn't have 500 zlotys.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We had a little bit less than that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But a change of clothes and things like this.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So I sneaked in the sewing machine under the clothes and under the storage we take with the horse and buggy.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
